            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-10-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="302"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                <head>302. Telegram 915 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d302fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/10–2055. Official Use
                        Only.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-10-20"
                            >October 20, 1955, 4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d302-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d302-1"/>
                <p>915. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Joint State USIA
                    message.</p>
                <p>Garnish informs me he has been assigned full time as Chief USIS Coverage Team
                    FONMIN Conference, and is departing Geneva immediately thereafter for home
                    leave. No information here on arrival his successor but appears may be at least
                    few weeks. With mass arrival correspondents for FONMIN Conference it can be
                    expected will be considerable increase in demands on information officer for my
                    talks. Thus important information officer with clear responsibility my talks be
                    available not later than October 26. From policy standpoint would not think it
                    desirable such officer be actively identified with FONMIN Conference. Would
                    appreciate Department promptly discussing appropriate action with USIA.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
